Alexander Steinkuehler vs Joseph Henry Blackburne
Manchester - (1863), Manchester ENG
Italian Game: Classical Variation. Greco Gambit Traditional Line (C54)

1. e4 Notes by Blackburne. 1... e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. c3 Nf6 5. d4 ed4 6. cd4 Bb4 7. Bd2 Bd2 8. Nfd2 A weak move. The other Knight ought to have taken. 8... Nd4 9. O-O d6 10. Nb3 Nb3 11. Qb3 O-O 12. Re1 Nh5 13. e5 Qg5 14. ed6 Nf4 15. Bf7 This tempting but unsound move led to all his subsequent troubles. 15... Kh8 16. g3 cd6 17. Nc3 Nh3 18. Kg2 Qf6 19. Bd5 Qf2 20. Kh1 Qg1 21. Rg1 Nf2 22. Kg2 Bh3# In chess language this is a "clean" mate and is considered one of the most beautiful ever produced in actual play.
